      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index directly maps to the regulatory submission QoI; traceability matrix linking model output to device performance specification provided.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the primary QoI in the 510(k) submission. Traceability matrix confirmed by regulatory affairs team."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry and fluid (bovine blood or blood analogue with matched viscosity) at VAD operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation used FDA generic pump geometry with porcine blood analogue at 37 °C; actual device uses a proprietary impeller geometry. Geometric similarity index 0.87, below required 0.95 threshold for level 4."
    },
